            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="enrollment">Product enrollment</h2>

<p>Products must be enrolled in the accessibility service before you can track accessibility issues, audits, and compliance.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enrolling a product</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Enroll product"</strong></li>
    <li>Search for and select the product from FIPS CMS</li>
    <li>Configure initial settings:
        <ul>
            <li>Complaints email address</li>
            <li>SLA settings</li>
            <li>Contact methods</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save the enrollment</li>
    <li>The product now appears in the accessibility dashboard</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Accessibility dashboard</h3>

<p>The accessibility dashboard provides an overview of all enrolled products:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Total enrolled products:</strong> Count of products in the service</li>
    <li><strong>Total open issues:</strong> Number of unresolved accessibility issues</li>
    <li><strong>Overdue issues:</strong> Issues past their planned resolution date</li>
    <li><strong>Total audit spend:</strong> Cumulative cost of accessibility audits</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="issues">Accessibility issues</h2>

<p>Track accessibility issues for enrolled products with WCAG criteria linking and resolution tracking.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating an accessibility issue</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to the product's accessibility detail page</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Issues</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Add issue"</strong></li>
    <li>Complete the issue form:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Brief description of the issue</li>
            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the accessibility problem</li>
            <li><strong>Issue level:</strong> Severity level (Critical, High, Medium, Low)</li>
            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Current status (New, Open, In progress, Resolved, Closed)</li>
            <li><strong>Planned resolution date:</strong> Target date for fixing the issue</li>
            <li><strong>WCAG criteria:</strong> Link to relevant WCAG success criteria (multi-select)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save the issue</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking to WCAG criteria</h3>

<p>Accessibility issues should be linked to the relevant WCAG success criteria:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Select one or more WCAG criteria when creating or editing an issue</li>
    <li>WCAG criteria are organised by level (A, AA, AAA) and guideline</li>
    <li>Linking helps track compliance and identify patterns</li>
    <li>The accessibility heatmap uses WCAG criteria links for analysis</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Managing issues</h3>

<p>Update issue status and track resolution:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Update status:</strong> Change status as work progresses</li>
    <li><strong>Add comments:</strong> Document progress and decisions</li>
    <li><strong>Request retest:</strong> Request a retest when an issue is fixed</li>
    <li><strong>Close issue:</strong> Close with explanation when resolved</li>
    <li><strong>View all issues:</strong> See all issues across all products with filtering</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="audits">Audit history</h2>

<p>Track accessibility audits conducted for products, including costs and audit reports.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Adding an audit</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to the product's accessibility detail page</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Audits</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Add audit"</strong></li>
    <li>Complete the audit form:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Audit date:</strong> Date the audit was conducted</li>
            <li><strong>Audit type:</strong> Type of audit (Full audit, Partial audit, Automated scan, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>Audited by:</strong> Name of the auditor or organisation</li>
            <li><strong>Cost:</strong> Cost of the audit (optional)</li>
            <li><strong>Report URL:</strong> Link to the audit report (optional)</li>
            <li><strong>Notes:</strong> Additional information about the audit</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Save the audit</li>
</ol>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing audit history</h3>

<p>The audit history shows all audits for a product in chronological order:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Audits are displayed with most recent first</li>
    <li>Total audit spend is calculated and displayed</li>
    <li>Filter audits by date range or type</li>
    <li>View audit reports via links</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="statements">Accessibility statements</h2>

<p>Manage accessibility statements for products and verify their publication.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Accessibility statement verification</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to the product's accessibility detail page</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Settings</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Find the <strong>Accessibility statement</strong> section</li>
    <li>Enter or verify the statement URL</li>
    <li>Mark the statement as verified</li>
    <li>Add notes about the statement</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> All public-facing digital services must have an accessibility statement published. The statement should be linked from the service's footer and comply with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>
</div>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="compliance">WCAG compliance</h2>

<p>Monitor WCAG compliance for products and track progress towards meeting accessibility standards.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">WCAG compliance tracking</h3>

<p>Track compliance with WCAG 2.1 standards:</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>WCAG level:</strong> Track compliance with Level A, AA, or AAA</li>
    <li><strong>Compliance status:</strong> Overall compliance status (Compliant, Partially compliant, Non-compliant)</li>
    <li><strong>Issues by criteria:</strong> View issues grouped by WCAG criteria</li>
    <li><strong>Progress tracking:</strong> Monitor progress towards full compliance</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">SLA management</h3>

<p>Configure and monitor service level agreements for accessibility:</p>

<ul>
    <li>Set SLA targets for issue resolution</li>
    <li>Track SLA compliance</li>
    <li>Monitor overdue issues</li>
    <li>Generate SLA reports</li>
</ul>

<hr class="my-4">

<h2 id="heatmap">Accessibility heatmap</h2>

<p>The accessibility heatmap provides a visual overview of accessibility issues across products and WCAG criteria.</p>

<h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using the heatmap</h3>

<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility → Heatmap</strong></li>
    <li>View issues grouped by:
        <ul>
            <li>WCAG criteria (showing which criteria have the most issues)</li>
            <li>Product (showing which products have the most issues)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Filter by issue level or WCAG criteria type</li>
    <li>Export heatmap data for analysis</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> The heatmap helps identify patterns in accessibility issues. Products with many issues against the same WCAG criteria may need additional training or tooling support.</p>
</div>

